    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-26T17:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-26T17:15:00-05:00" n="762"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.24/836: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-26T18:15:00-04:00"
                            >February 26, 1944—6:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–162. The War Department has received General Brett’s<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d762fn6">Gen. George H. Brett, Commanding General, Caribbean Defense
                        Command.</note> recommendations covering the allotment to Colombia of
                    military equipment to which you refer in your despatch 3235 of January 19 and
                    your telegram 115 of January 22.<note n="7" xml:id="d762fn7">Neither
                        printed.</note> These recommendations have received the careful
                    consideration of the War Department which has informed General Brett that it
                    approves the delivery to Colombia of the following equipment: <table cols="2"
                        rows="20">
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 4.5em">
                                <hi rend="italic">Item</hi>
                            </cell>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 4.5em">
                                <hi rend="italic">Quantity</hi>
                            </cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Light Trucks 1½ T</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">20</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Light Trucks ½ T.W.C</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">19</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Motorcycles</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">15</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Launches, motor</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap"> 2 J–340 series</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">75 guns</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">20</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">37 Anti Tank</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">12</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Mortars 60mm</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap"> 3 with mount</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">M.G. 30 Hv</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">24 Model 1917 A–l</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Rifle, automatic, Cal. 30</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">189 M–1918 A–2</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. (SC 75 mm.)</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">2400</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. (NC 75 mm.)</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">9600</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. (RC 75 mm.)</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">7200</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. smoke (WP 75 mm.)</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">2400</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. 37 mm. gun</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">360</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shot Armor piercing M–74 37 mm.
                                gun</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">3000</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Shell H.E. 60 mm. mortar</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">675</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Cartridge AP (or ball) and tracer Cal. 30
                                (belted 4 to 1) M.G</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">71400</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Cartridge AP (or ball) Cal. 30</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">204120</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell rend="padding-left: 3em">Cartridge tracer Cal. 30</cell>
                            <cell rendition="#nowrap">51030</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>The Department understands that all of this material will be forwarded to
                    Colombia from the Canal Zone. It forms a portion of a list submitted to the
                    Department by the Colombian Embassy bearing <pb facs="0819" n="805"
                        xml:id="pg_805"/> the signature of Colonel Faris, former Chief of the United
                    States Military Mission to Colombia. This list also comprises certain
                    quartermaster material which the Colombian Government desires to obtain. As
                    General Brett’s recommendations contain no reference to this equipment, the
                    Department has requested the War Department to ask him whether this matter also
                    is receiving his consideration.</p>
                <p>The Colombian Embassy has also presented a list of about 100 landplanes and
                    seaplanes for training, combat and transport purposes. The Department will
                    consult with the War and Navy Departments on this matter and will keep you
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
